-- Areva, Siemens Win Enel Contract for Nuclear Reactor System, Echos Says
-- David Whitehouse
-- 2010-04-26T04:44:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-04-26/areva-siemens-win-nuclear-control-command-contract-from-enel-echos-says.html

          
          
              Areva SA and Siemens AG have won a
contract to supply a nuclear-reactor control-command system to
Enel SpA, French daily Les Echos reported, without citing
anyone.  
 The contract is to supply the system for two Russian
nuclear reactors and has a value in the dozens of millions of
euros, according to the newspaper.  
          
          


  


        